**Problem:** Even with authentication added, the current design has no concept of *who* can see *what*. Any authenticated user can retrieve all users' data.

**Fix:** Add a role-based authorization layer.

```js
function authorize(...roles) {
  return (req, res, next) => {
    if (!roles.includes(req.user?.role)) {
      return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Insufficient permissions' });
    }
    next();
  };
}

