```js
// FIXED — add helmet before any route definitions
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());
// For finer control over individual headers:
app.use(helmet.hsts({ maxAge: 31536000, includeSubDomains: true }));
```

**c) No CORS policy defined.**
Express does not set CORS headers by default, but if this API is later fronted by a browser client, the absence of an explicit policy is a misconfiguration waiting to happen.

```bash
npm install cors
```
```js
